cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is about generating adversarial examples in the natural language domain, specifically for sentiment analysis and textual entailment models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep neural networks, which suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the vulnerability of DNNs to adversarial attacks, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
